cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on wireless edge networks and video streaming over these networks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a reinforcement learning approach to optimize the network performance. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper uses video streaming as a use case. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a feedback loop system for network optimization. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of network configurations on Quality of Experience (QoE).
